{
  "texts": [
    "For NEnF, we used R = σ 2 diag{H μt|t-1 }; for RB-SMC 2, this quantity was further scaled by a factor of 2.",
    "We performed a single run of these schemes with M = 20, 000 particles and N = 20 initial ensemble members.",
    "An initial condition of x 0 = (4631, 240, 37413, 1400, -10, -10.5) ′ was assumed to be fixed and known for each run.",
    "We followed Section 5.2 by sampling p (θ) t (x t |x t-1) through recursive draws of the Euler-Maruyama approximation (26) with ∆t = 0.1.",
    "The conditions for triggering a resample-move step and increasing N were as Section 5.1."
  ]
}